//- Main document response details, collected by browsertime whenever
//- a HAR exists (zero config; sensitive headers are always removed):
//- the final URL after redirects, the response status, the redirect
//- count and the response headers. Handy for spotting cache status
//- (x-cache/age), CDN pops and experiment enrollment (server-timing)
//- without opening the HAR. The card is omitted on older browsertime
//- data or with --skipHar. Cells carry `data-title` so the responsive
//- mobile stack labels each value.
if mainDocument
  - const mainDocumentHeaders = Object.entries(mainDocument.headers || {})
  a#main-document
  .listing-card
    .listing-card-header
      h3.listing-card-title Main document
      span.listing-card-meta status #{mainDocument.status} · #{h.plural(mainDocument.redirects, 'redirect')}
    p.listing-card-help
      a(href=mainDocument.url, title=mainDocument.url) #{mainDocument.url}
    if mainDocumentHeaders.length > 0
      .responsive
        table(data-sortable)
          thead
            tr
              th Header
              th Value
          tbody
            each header in mainDocumentHeaders
              tr
                td(data-title='Header')
                  code.server-timing-name #{header[0]}
                td(data-title='Value') #{header[1]}
